===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|roten}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{m|non|rotinn||decayed, rotten}}, past participle of an unrecorded verb related to {{cog|non|rotna||to rot}} and {{cog|ang|rotian||to rot}}, ultimately from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*rutōną||to rot}}. More at {{l|en|rot}}.

